	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Marietta O.</placeName> <date>Friday March 5&#44; 1858</date>.</p>
				<p>Rev. &#38; Dear Sir</p>
				<p rend="indent(2)">I <sic>inclose</sic> six dollars to you&#44;<lb/> hoping it will reach you safely.  As I now<lb/> have a family to support&#44; and serve a congrega&#61;<lb/>tion who are far back in supporting me&#44; and am<lb/> pressed for funds&#44; I feel as if I must say to you<lb/> that I feel unable to take the &#8220;Occident&#8221; any<lb/> longer.  You will please therefore discontinue<lb/> it.  Probably in better circumstances I will<lb/> take it again.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">It is pleasant to reflect on the politeness<lb/> which we have maintained towards each other&#44; though<lb/> occupying adverse standpoints.  Am always pleased<lb/> to hear from you.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I try to watch the development of the des&#61;<lb/>tiny of <placeName>Israel</placeName> in these <placeName>U. S.</placeName> with great<lb/> interest and sincere prayer.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Yours most respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">M. R. Miller</persName>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
